SIMPLE: termer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Termer
<hw>Term"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
resorted to London during the law term only, in order to practice
tricks, to carry on intrigues, or the like.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>termor</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who has an estate for a term of
years or for life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Termes</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
